ccsniff --continuation-discipline detection (2026-06-01): the discriminator between a real toolless-turn stop and benign think-then-act is stop_reason. An assistant message ending in "Let me X" but with stop_reason=tool_use had a tool follow and is NOT a stop; only stop_reason=end_turn ending in a text block is the harness halting on prose. Implementation: index.js propagates msgId+stopReason onto each emitted block; cli.js groups by msgId, gates on stopReason===end_turn, extracts the LAST sentence and flags if it STARTS with a deferred-intent/summary phrase (testing the whole multi-paragraph blob with a start-anchor fails). Validated 14 true-positive cross-project stops (streamtts "I will report back when build finishes" is textbook), zero false positives. tv8 itself emitted 0 - it was IDLE mid-EXECUTE (16min gap, last msg stop_reason=tool_use), NOT permanently stopped. Two distinct shapes need two detectors: runtime watchdog (idle>300s mid-chain) + ccsniff transcript rule (toolless end_turn).